De acuerdo con el CEO de Telefónica Movistar Colombia, Fabián Hernández, esta estará habilitada en el 50% del territorio nacional en la red NB IoT (Narrowband Internet of Things) y LTE - M (Conectividad de la red de baja potencia y largo alcance).

WAN –Range Up to 50km
Existing 3G and 4G networks and the newer 5G will be used
Low powered alternatives that are being developed by he mobile carrier networks.
    LTE-MTC also called LTE-M and LTE Cat M1
    Narrow band IOT. –NB-IOT
    https://www.link-labs.com/blog/lte-iot-technologies

Protocols
    HTTP
    MQTT– (Message Queuing Telemetry Transport) Uses TCP/IP.
    	Main IOT messaging protocol because it is lightweight and easy to use.
	Publish subscribe model (P/S) requires a message broker (switch).
    AMQP -( Advanced Message Queuing Protocol) Uses TCP/IP.
	Publish subscribe model and Point to Point .
    COAP-(Constrained Application Protocol)
	Uses UDP designed specifically for IOT uses request response model
	like HTTP. RFC 7252
    DDS– (Data Distribution Service) –
    XMPP for instant messaging (IM) to connect people to other people via text messages 

Protocol Support by Platform
    Microsooft Azure -MQTT,AMQP,HTTP and HTTPS
    AWS -MQTT,HTTPS,MQTT over websockets
    IBM Bluemix – MQTT,HTTPS,MQTT
    Thingwrox -MQTT,HTTPS,MQTT,AMQP

MQTT
CONNECT, PUBLISH, SUBSCRIBE, UNSUBSCRIBE and DISCONNECT types 

A hub-and-spoke architecture is natural for MQTT.
All the devices connect to a data concentrator server, like IBM’s new
MessageSight appliance. Works on top of TCP, which provides a simple, reliable stream. Since the IT infrastructure uses the data, the entire system is
designed to easily transport data into enterprise technologies like ActiveMQ
and enterprise service buses (ESBs).

